  "elapsed_s": 55.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Julishka ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Neni, ?] which means Aunt Julia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember her quite well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strictly Hungarian, although my mother was speaking German fluently as well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because from her background, the Schleyers, Albert Schleyer, after whom got my first name, was of German background.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he hardly spoke Hungarian and was very, very much proud and, and, and, and, and very much observing his German heritage.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, as my mother told me, that he never permitted at the dinner table any other conversation in his presence but German.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he said it's not polite in the presence of your father to talk a language which he doesn't understand and didn't master.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prior to the time what you call the occupation, which needs to be cleared a little bit, because Hungary was actually a willing partner of Germany.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Germany came into Hungary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But historically, it's a different issue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was with some mutual agreement between the two country's leaders.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Hungary was a, a willing partner in World War II to fight on the German side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in that household, we had my mother, my father, and my grandmother, my mother's mother, who lived with us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was not so easy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father lost his business, which was a good and thriving business, and lost his business because in Hungary, after I was born in 1928 and few years later, started-- the country published anti-Jewish laws to restrict Jewish people's businesses, opportunities for education.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Schooling was curbed-- higher education I am referring to.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so was the permits to own your own businesses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the time that you asked, at the time of-- during World War II and during the time when the Nazi forces moved into Hungary.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
